        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Any type of RPG, that is, a game that has room for character progression/advancement, is going to cater to power-gamers, whether intentional or not.  By it's very design, advancement is (must be) a time-consuming process, so those people that spend 12 hours a day playing will always come out ahead of the casual gamer.  It's just how the system works.</P><P></P><P><img src="http://www.onethirtyeight.com/graphics-2/cg.gif"></font></td>
