 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Serrin</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> There's a few ways they could do it.</P><P>A) Develop characters by something out of PC control. Growth over time, based on cycles, random, or anything else like that.</P><P>B) Don't let characters develop, at all.</P><P>c) Let the players THINK they're developing characters when they're actually limited by something out of their control. For example, say you can only gain a level a week, and the average person could earn a level in 3 hours.</P><P>And yes, Fallout 2 rocked.</font></td>
