      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Drexyll</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Years ago (before EQ) there was a 2D game called "The Realm" that was a fantasy RPG type of game, and it exemplifies why that kind of system wouldnt work.  Eventually everyone in the game got to be the same lvl.  The driving force to play then became accumulating/hoarding wealth and items.  Once everyone figures out that they can only lvl once a week, for example, many people will either cease to play as much (which the designers would NEVER go for), or they'd just focus all their time that couldn't go to leveling on getting rich, and thus the "powergamers" would still be ahead of the casual player.  I guess the solution to that would be to limit the wealth/loot people could get, but now you're making a pretty boring game, with no reason to play very often.  Sounds like an FPS, or an old "so many turns per day" BBS door game.</P><P></P><P><img src="http://www.onethirtyeight.com/graphics-2/cg.gif"></font></td>
      </tr>
