        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I too thought one way to work it out would be to limit the number of levels you can get within a certain timeframe.  That way the people who play 24/7, don't work, don't bathe, don't socialize, etc. wouldn't be able to level any faster than normal people.</P><P>But I don't think it's necessary when you've got over a dozen different classes.  NOTHING is ever going to stop powergamers.  Look at those idiots who farmed VT keys for six months.  They bitched about the timesink but it was their own damn fault for being so pathetically depraved.  Cut the inhuman time investment and prepare to welcome twice as many subscribers into the fold.  Let the powergamers dictate the gameplay and you'll never get out of this niche.</P><P> </font></td>
